# Petri Net Model

## Data Structures

### PetriNet
```typescript
interface PetriNet {
  id: string
  name: string
  places: Place[]
  transitions: Transition[]
  arcs: Arc[]
  operators: Operator[]      // WoPeD-specific workflow operators
  subProcesses: SubProcess[] // Hierarchical nets
}
```

### Elements
```typescript
interface Place {
  id: string
  name: string
  position: { x: number, y: number }
  tokens: number  // Initial marking
}

interface Transition {
  id: string
  name: string
  position: { x: number, y: number }
  label?: string
  triggers?: Trigger[]  // Time/Resource/Message triggers
}

interface Arc {
  id: string
  sourceId: string   // Place, Transition, Operator or SubProcess
  targetId: string
  weight: number     // Default: 1
}

interface Operator {
  id: string
  type: OperatorType  // AND_SPLIT, XOR_JOIN, etc.
  position: { x: number, y: number }
  label?: string
}

interface SubProcess {
  id: string
  name: string
  position: { x: number, y: number }
  subNetId: string   // Reference to nested PetriNet
}
```

## Operator Types
| Type | Symbol | Description |
|------|--------|-------------|
| AND_SPLIT | ◇→ | Parallel branching |
| AND_JOIN | →◇ | Synchronization |
| XOR_SPLIT | ⊗→ | Exclusive choice |
| XOR_JOIN | →⊗ | Simple merge |
| AND_SPLIT_JOIN | ◇◇ | Combined |
| XOR_SPLIT_JOIN | ⊗⊗ | Combined |

## Validation
- Arcs always connect Place↔Transition (or Operator/SubProcess)
- No direct Place→Place or Transition→Transition connections
- Arc weights must be ≥ 1
- IDs must be unique (nanoid)

## Canvas Rendering
- Places: Circles (radius: 20)
- Transitions: Rectangles (40x30)
- Operators: Diamonds (30x30)
- SubProcesses: Rectangles with double border
- Tokens: Small black dots inside places

## Store Actions
```typescript
// Add elements
store.addPlace({ x, y })
store.addTransition({ x, y })
store.addArc(sourceId, targetId)

// Selection
store.selectElement(id)
store.clearSelection()

// Navigation (subprocesses)
store.navigateToSubProcess(subProcessId)
store.navigateUp()
```
